uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model

Enum IEditability

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<IEditability>
      • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.IEditability
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<IEditability>

    public enum IEditability
extends java.lang.Enum<IEditability>
    Represents the editability from the client perspective of a particular ISlot. Covers slot editability status for both concrete and abstract values (see IValue.abstractValue())

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CONCRETE_ONLY
      Slot can only be given concrete values by the client.
      FULL
      Slot can be given both concrete and abstract values by the client.
      NONE
      Slot is not editable by the client.

      • getAssertionsStrongest

        public IEditability getAssertionsStrongest(IEditability other)
        Provides the "strongest" editability status between this and the other specified value, for slots on assertion frames. The strongest status is the one that will take precedence when two competing statuses are provided for a single slot. Precedence order for query slots, strongest first is:
        1. NONE
        2. FULL
        3. CONCRETE_ONLY (the default value, hence the weakest)
        Parameters:
        other - Editability status to test against this one
        Returns:
        Strongest editability status for slots on assertion frames

      • getQueriesStrongest

        public IEditability getQueriesStrongest(IEditability other)
        Provides the "strongest" editability status between this and the other specified value, for slots on query frames. The strongest status is the one that will take precedence when two competing statuses are provided for a single slot. Precedence order for query slots, strongest first is:
        1. NONE
        2. CONCRETE_ONLY
        3. FULL (the default value, hence the weakest)
        Parameters:
